1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper focuses on the feasibility of ultra-low latency for 5G, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. The use of novel frame structure and signaling procedure also suggests a networking focus. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of hybrid automatic repeat request (HARQ) and round trip time (RTT), which are concepts related to information theory. 

3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The lab trial may have involved the use of specialized hardware to achieve the ultra-low latency, which would fall under the hardware architecture sub-category. 

4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Ultra-low latency is important for multimedia applications such as video streaming and online gaming, which may be a focus of this paper. 

5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The use of novel frame structure and signaling procedure may involve system design and control, which would fall under this sub-category.
